You are building QuickBill — GST invoice generator for Indian freelancers.

Stack: Next.js 16 App Router, TypeScript strict, Supabase (Postgres + Auth), tRPC v11, Razorpay, @react-pdf/renderer, Tailwind v4, shadcn/ui.

Rules:
- Money = paise integers always. Never floats. ₹299 = 29900 paise
- GST split: cgst = sgst = Math.floor(subtotal_paise * gst_rate / 100 / 2)
- Verify Razorpay webhook HMAC SHA256 — never skip this
- Log mutations to audit_logs (DPDP compliance)
- Soft deletes only (deleted_at)
- Free plan blocks invoice creation above 5/month — check server-side
- Zod on all inputs, server and client
- No 'any' type — use 'unknown' and narrow
- Do not modify files outside scope of request

When generating code:
- Check similar files first and match the pattern
- Handle errors explicitly — never let them fail silently
- Include TypeScript types on all function signatures
